---
# https://forum.posit.co/t/when-to-use-yaml-vs-when-to-use-setup-code-chunk/56169/
title: "`r params$doc_title`"
author: "MHKim"
date: "`r Sys.setlocale('LC_ALL', 'en_US.utf8'); format(Sys.time(), '%B %d, %Y')`"
output:
  html_notebook:  
    toc: yes
    toc_depth: 6
    toc_float:
      collapsed: false
      smooth_scroll: false
    number_sections: false
    code_folding: none
    df_print: tibble
    highlight: textmate
    fig_width: 10
    fig_height: 6
  html_document:
    toc: yes
    toc_depth: 6
    toc_float:
      collapsed: false
      smooth_scroll: false
    number_sections: false
    df_print: tibble
    code_folding: none
    highlight: textmate
    fig_width: 10
    fig_height: 6
  pdf_document: 
    toc: yes
    toc_depth: 6
    fig_width: 10
    fig_height: 6
    latex_engine: xelatex  # mainfont, sansfont, monofont, mathfont works only with xelatex and lualatex, but not pdflatex
    keep_tex: true
  word_document:
    toc: yes
    toc_depth: 6
    fig_width: 9
    fig_height: 6
# documentclass: scrartcl  # https://pandoc.org/MANUAL.html#variables-for-latex
# classoption: fontsize=9pt 
geometry: portrait, a3paper, margin=20mm # https://bookdown.org/yihui/rmarkdown/pdf-document.html#latex-options
# fontsize: 12pt
header-includes: 
  - \usepackage{fontspec}
  - \newcommand{\setfallbackfont}[4]{
      \IfFontExistsTF{#2}
        {#1{#2}}
        {\IfFontExistsTF{#3}
          {#1{#3}}
          {#1{#4}}}}
  # - \setfallbackfont{\setmainfont}{Roboto Condensed}{Noto Sans Condensed}{Arial Narrow}
  # - \setfallbackfont{\setsansfont}{Roboto Condensed}{Noto Sans Condensed}{Arial Narrow}
  - \setfallbackfont{\setmainfont}{Roboto}{Noto Sans}{Arial}
  - \setfallbackfont{\setsansfont}{Roboto}{Noto Sans}{Arial}
  - \setfallbackfont{\setmonofont}{Cascadia Code SemiBold}{Cascadia Code}{Fira Code}
  - \usepackage[hangul]{kotex}
  - \setfallbackfont{\setmainhangulfont}{NanumGothic}{HCR Dotum LVT}{Malgun Gothic}
  - \setfallbackfont{\setsanshangulfont}{NanumGothic}{HCR Dotum LVT}{Malgun Gothic}
  - \setfallbackfont{\setmonohangulfont}{D2Coding}{NanumGothicCoding}{NanumGothic}
params:
  doc_title: !r basename(rstudioapi::getSourceEditorContext()$path)

```{r, echo=TRUE, results="markup", collapse=TRUE, paged.print=FALSE, comment="#", R.options=list(width=120)}
options(width=120)
.packagename = "tidyverse"; if (!paste0("package:",.packagename) %in% search()) {library(.packagename, character.only = TRUE)}
# suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(survival))
for(.packagename in c("survminer")) {if(!require(.packagename,character.only=TRUE)) install.packages(.packagename)  ;  library(.packagename,character.only=TRUE)}  
# ?survival::lung
.objectname = DataSetName = "analyticDF_time2event"
assign(
    DataSetName, 
    survival::lung |> as_tibble() |> mutate(event = as.logical(status-1), Group = c("Male", "Female")[sex] |> as.factor(), StudyPopulation = time >= 30) |>
        # dplyr::select(-status, -sex)
        dplyr::select(-status)
)
analyticDF_time2event %>% {cat(" > ",deparse(substitute(.))," |> as_tibble() |> print()","  \n", sep=""); print(as_tibble(.))}
```

### df_5vars_10obs |> group_by(Group) |> summarise_all() ----  
```{r, echo=TRUE, results="markup", collapse=TRUE, paged.print=FALSE, comment="#", R.options=list(width=120)}

library(glmnet)
library(flextable)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)


input_data = df_5vars_10obs

# Prepare the predictor matrix X and response vector y
X <- input_data %>%
  select(-Group) %>%
  select_if(is.numeric) %>%
  drop_na()

# Extract y
y <- input_data$Group[complete.cases(input_data[, c("Group", names(X))])]

# Convert y to a factor and then to numeric
y_numeric <- as.numeric(factor(y)) - 1  # Now y_numeric contains 0s and 1s

# Standardize predictors
X_scaled <- scale(X)

# Perform Elastic Net regression with cross-validation
cv_model <- cv.glmnet(
  x = as.matrix(X_scaled),
  y = y_numeric,
  family = "binomial",
  alpha = 0.5,
  standardize = FALSE
)

# Extract coefficients at the lambda that gives minimum cross-validated error
coef_min <- coef(cv_model, s = "lambda.min")
coef_min_matrix <- as.matrix(coef_min)

# Print the coefficient matrix
print(coef_min_matrix)

# Extract coefficients at lambda.1se
coef_1se <- coef(cv_model, s = "lambda.1se")
coef_1se_matrix <- as.matrix(coef_1se)

# Print the coefficient matrix
print(coef_1se_matrix)


# # Identify selected variables (non-zero coefficients excluding intercept)
# selected_vars <- rownames(coef_min_matrix)[coef_min_matrix[, 1] != 0]
# selected_vars <- selected_vars[selected_vars != "(Intercept)"]

# Define a threshold for considering coefficients as zero
threshold <- 1e-6

# # Identify selected variables (non-zero coefficients excluding intercept)
# selected_vars <- rownames(coef_min_matrix)[abs(coef_min_matrix[, 1]) > threshold]
# selected_vars <- selected_vars[selected_vars != "(Intercept)"]

selected_vars <- rownames(coef_1se_matrix)[abs(coef_1se_matrix[, 1]) > threshold]
selected_vars <- selected_vars[selected_vars != "(Intercept)"]

# Print selected variables
print(selected_vars)

if (length(selected_vars) == 0) {
  stop("No variables were selected by the model.")
}

# Prepare the summary statistics table
summary_table <- input_data %>%
  select(Group, all_of(selected_vars)) %>%
  group_by(Group) %>%
  summarise_all(
    list(
      Mean = ~ mean(., na.rm = TRUE),
      SD = ~ sd(., na.rm = TRUE),
      Median = ~ median(., na.rm = TRUE),
      Min = ~ min(., na.rm = TRUE),
      Max = ~ max(., na.rm = TRUE)
    )
  ) %>%
  pivot_longer(
    -Group,
    names_to = c("Variable", "Statistic"),
    names_sep = "_"
  ) %>%
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = "Statistic",
    values_from = "value"
  )

# Display the summary table
print(summary_table)

```

#### lambda_seq <- 10^seq(2, -2, by = -0.1) ----  
```{r, echo=TRUE, results="markup", collapse=TRUE, paged.print=FALSE, comment="#", R.options=list(width=120)}
options(width=120)
# Set a custom lambda sequence
lambda_seq <- 10^seq(2, -2, by = -0.1)

# Perform Elastic Net regression with custom lambda
cv_model <- cv.glmnet(
  x = as.matrix(X_scaled),
  y = y_numeric,
  family = "binomial",
  alpha = 0.5,
  lambda = lambda_seq,
  standardize = FALSE
)

# Use the largest lambda that results in a model with desired sparsity
```

```{r, echo=TRUE, results="markup", collapse=TRUE, paged.print=FALSE, comment="#", R.options=list(width=120)}
options(width=120)
library(glmnet)
library(flextable)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)

create_table1 <- function(dataset, byVar, alpha = 1, output_as_flextable = FALSE) {
  # Convert byVar to factor
  dataset[[byVar]] <- as.factor(dataset[[byVar]])
  
  # Prepare predictor matrix X and response y
  X <- dataset %>%
    select(-all_of(byVar)) %>%
    select_if(is.numeric) %>%
    drop_na()
  
  y <- dataset[[byVar]][complete.cases(dataset[, c(byVar, names(X))])]
  y_numeric <- as.numeric(factor(y)) - 1
  
  # Standardize predictors
  X_scaled <- scale(X)
  
  # Perform Elastic Net regression
  cv_model <- cv.glmnet(
    x = as.matrix(X_scaled),
    y = y_numeric,
    family = "binomial",
    alpha = alpha,
    standardize = FALSE
  )
  
  # Extract coefficients at lambda.1se
  coef_1se <- coef(cv_model, s = "lambda.1se")
  coef_1se_matrix <- as.matrix(coef_1se)
  
  # Define threshold
  threshold <- 1e-6
  
  # Identify selected variables
  selected_vars <- rownames(coef_1se_matrix)[abs(coef_1se_matrix[, 1]) > threshold]
  selected_vars <- selected_vars[selected_vars != "(Intercept)"]
  
  # Check if any variables were selected
  if (length(selected_vars) == 0) {
    stop("No variables were selected by the model.")
  }
  
  # Prepare summary table
  summary_table <- dataset %>%
    select(all_of(byVar), all_of(selected_vars)) %>%
    group_by_at(byVar) %>%
    summarise_all(
      list(
        Mean = ~ mean(., na.rm = TRUE),
        SD = ~ sd(., na.rm = TRUE),
        Median = ~ median(., na.rm = TRUE),
        Min = ~ min(., na.rm = TRUE),
        Max = ~ max(., na.rm = TRUE)
      )
    ) %>%
    pivot_longer(
      -all_of(byVar),
      names_to = c("Variable", "Statistic"),
      names_sep = "_"
    ) %>%
    pivot_wider(
      names_from = "Statistic",
      values_from = "value"
    )
  
  if (output_as_flextable) {
    # Create flextable
    ft <- flextable(summary_table)
    ft <- autofit(ft)
    return(ft)
  } else {
    return(summary_table)
  }
}
```
